Assam: Several trains cancelled due to agitation in Assam 
22-2-2017 
GUWAHATI: A "Rail Roko" agitation called by two adivasi militant outfits has paralysed rail communication in Assam . At least 12 long-distance trains, including three Rajdhani trains have been affected.The Northeast Frontier Railway stated that eight other trains have been cancelled due to the agitation.A railway spokesman said that at 6.55am about 50 picketers arrived at Kokrajhar station, the last major station in Assam near the border with West Bengal, and blocked the railway track.The rail road has been called by Adivasi Ceasefire Organisation and Birsa Commando Force. 
